The article is a statement and release about the passing of Congressman John Lewis. It recognizes Lewis as a great man who had a significant impact on America through his courage and years of public service. The statement highlights his role as a leader in the civil rights movement and praises his selflessness and conviction. The author also mentions that Lewis was a colleague and friend, and reflects on the privilege of crossing the Edmund Pettus Bridge with him. The statement concludes with prayers and deepest sympathies for Lewis' family and friends, and hopes that his memory and example will continue to inspire.